== Thread safety ==

=== Atomic operations ===

Atomic blocks use a light-red colour. Atomics allow safe read-modify-write operations across shader threads.

{| class="wikitable" style="width:100%"
! Block !! Type !! Description
|-
| <code>Load atomic [ATOMIC]</code> || Reporter || Performs an <code>atomicLoad</code> on a pointer-to-atomic and returns the value. Pass a '''Pointer to variable''' block.
|-
| <code>Perform operation [OP] on atomic [ATOMIC] with value [VALUE]</code> (command) || Command || Performs an atomic operation and discards the result.
|-
| <code>Perform operation [OP] on atomic [ATOMIC] with value [VALUE]</code> (reporter) || Reporter || Performs an atomic operation and returns the old value.
|}

Available atomic operations:

{| class="wikitable"
! Operation !! Effect
|-
| <code>atomicStore</code> || Stores <code>VALUE</code> to the atomic.
|-
| <code>atomicAdd</code> || Atomically adds <code>VALUE</code>; returns old value.
|-
| <code>atomicSub</code> || Atomically subtracts <code>VALUE</code>; returns old value.
|-
| <code>atomicMax</code> || Atomically keeps the maximum; returns old value.
|-
| <code>atomicMin</code> || Atomically keeps the minimum; returns old value.
|-
| <code>atomicAnd</code> || Atomically bitwise-ANDs; returns old value.
|-
| <code>atomicOr</code> || Atomically bitwise-ORs; returns old value.
|-
| <code>atomicXor</code> || Atomically bitwise-XORs; returns old value.
|-
| <code>atomicExchange</code> || Swaps with <code>VALUE</code>; returns old value.
|-
| <code>atomicCompareExchangeWeak</code> || CAS operation; returns struct with old value and exchange status.
|}

