== Example: double every element in an array ==

This example allocates a 3-element float array, doubles each element on the GPU, and reads the result back.

=== Setup ===

<pre>
when green flag clicked
Reconnect to GPU

// ArrayBuffer with input data [1, 2, 3]
Create arraybuffer and view called [data] from array [[1, 2, 3]] of type (Float32Array v)

// GPU buffer: storage + copy_src (132 = 128 | 4)
Create buffer called [gpuData] with size(in bytes) [12] and usage flags [132]

// Staging buffer for readback: map_read + copy_dst (9 = 1 | 8)
Create buffer called [staging] with size(in bytes) [12] and usage flags [9]

// Bind group layout
Create bind group layout called [myBGL]
    Add bind group layout entry with binding [0] for type (buffer v) and descriptor
        (Buffer layout entry descriptor with usage type (storage v))

// Bind group
Create bind group called [myBG] using layout [myBGL]
    Add bind group entry with binding [0] of type (buffer v) using resource named [gpuData]

compile shaders
</pre>

=== Shader hat ===

<pre>
Define shader [double] using bind group layout [myBGL]
    Bind shader resource # [0] to variable [data] with settings [storage, read_write] type [array<f32>]
    Computer shader with workgroup size [[64]]
        declare var variable as [idx] with value
            (In object [global_invocation_id] get property [x]) : (auto v)
        Variable [data] [+=]
            (In object [data] get index (Get variable [idx]))
</pre>

=== Run and read back ===

<pre>
// Upload CPU data to GPU
Write [3] elements of data from arraybuffer [data] to buffer [gpuData] from offset [0] to offset [0]

// Dispatch 1 workgroup (covers 3 elements, workgroup_size is 64)
Run shader [double] using bind group [myBG] dimensions x: [1] y: [1] z: [1]

// Copy to staging buffer and read back
Copy [12] bytes of data from buffer [gpuData] from position [0] to buffer [staging] at position [0]
Read buffer [staging] to arraybuffer [result]
View arraybuffer [result] as (Float32Array v) called [resultView]

say (Get view [resultView] as array)  // expect [2, 4, 6]
</pre>

== Notes and known limitations ==

* '''Compute shaders only.''' Fragment/vertex shaders are not supported. Texture samplers do not work in compute shaders and are therefore hidden.
* '''Buffer offsets are in bytes.''' When using <code>copyBufferToBuffer</code> or <code>writeBuffer</code>, double-check whether the offset parameter is in bytes or elements — the block text says "bytes" where applicable.
* '''Buffer sizes must be multiples of 4.''' This is a WebGPU requirement.
* '''MAP_READ buffers cannot be STORAGE buffers.''' Always use a two-buffer approach: a STORAGE buffer for the shader, and a separate MAP_READ | COPY_DST staging buffer to read results back.
* '''miyo's buffer extension integration.''' If the <code>0znzwBuffers</code> extension is also loaded, GPU.sb3 will automatically detect it and you can reference its buffers.
* '''Error events.''' Unhandled GPU errors (device lost, validation errors) trigger the <code>when error thrown</code> hat. Always include error handling in production projects.

